# Trocado / Cordato — manual HTTP requests (REST Client / JetBrains HTTP Client)
#
# Start the app first:  uv run poe serve   (uvicorn on 127.0.0.1:8000, hot-reload)
# Then click "Send Request" above each block. Swagger UI: http://127.0.0.1:8000/schema/swagger
#
# Flow: sign-up (or sign-in) → copy the `token` from the response → paste into @token below.
# All routes live under the /v1 version prefix. Store is in-memory (data lost on restart).

@host = http://127.0.0.1:8000
@token = <paste-token-here>

### ── Authentication ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Sign up — create account and receive a session → 201 Created
POST {{host}}/v1/authentication/sign-up
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ana Silva",
  "email": "ana@example.com",
  "password": "senha-segura-123"
}

### Sign in — verify credentials and receive a session → 200 OK
POST {{host}}/v1/authentication/sign-in
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ana@example.com",
  "password": "senha-segura-123"
}

### Sign out — revoke the current session → 204 No Content
POST {{host}}/v1/authentication/sign-out
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ── Budgets ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create a budget (happy path) → 201 Created
POST {{host}}/v1/budgets
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "amount": "500.00",
  "start_date": "2026-06-01",
  "end_date": "2026-06-30",
  "note": "mercado"
}

### Create a budget without a note (note is optional) → 201 Created
POST {{host}}/v1/budgets
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "amount": "1200.00",
  "start_date": "2026-07-01",
  "end_date": "2026-07-31"
}
